UNITED STATES ex rel. Sanopik AGEMIAN, Relator-Appellant, v. Benjamin M. DAY, as Commissioner, etc., Respondent-Appellee. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 17, 1928. No. 227. V. H. Kalenderian, of New York City, for appellant. Sam’l C. Coleman and Charles H. Tuttle, both of New York City, for appellee.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed in open court.
